<LP>
   HUDSON, N.H. -- Howtek Inc. said it signed an agreement
with Adobe Systems Inc. to combine Howtek's Personal Color
scanner with Adobe's Photoshop Limited Edition, a special
version of Adobe's Photoshop software.
   Howtek said the combination of the two products will allow
personal computers to use color for such applications as
business graphics, presentations and color desktop
publishing.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The product will be available for shipment by the end of
October and will retail for about $2,595.
   Howtek makes computer products for the color graphics
market. Adobe is a software concern based in Palo Alto,
Calif.
